1. Hardware Load Balancer

Physical device used in data centers.

Features
High performance
Expensive
Used by large companies
Example
F5 Networks

Users → Hardware Load Balancer → Servers

2. Software Load Balancer

Software application installed on a server or cloud.

Features
Low cost
Flexible
Easy to configure
Examples
NGINX
HAProxy
Users → NGINX/HAProxy → Multiple Servers

Types Based on OSI Layer
3. Layer 4 Load Balancer

Works at Transport Layer.

Uses
IP Address
TCP/UDP Port
Features
Faster
Less intelligent routing
Example
Request → Based on IP + Port